text: Merced County ( ) is a county in the northern San Joaquin Valley section of the Central Valley, in the U.S. state of California. As of the 2020 census, the population was 281,202. The county seat is Merced. The county is named after the Merced River. It is located north of Fresno County and Fresno, and southeast of Santa Clara County and San Jose. == References == == Other websites == * Merced County Official Website Category:1850s establishments in California Category:1855 establishments in the United States
